Input: 

Read a month name from the user.

Process:

Convert the first letter of user entered month to upper case and rest to lower case. 
Assign a month number (1-12) to the month according to its name using a conditional statements (Switch case).
Also use -1 for invalid user entered month. 

Output: 

Display the month name (January to December) or "invalid" and its ordinal number (1st to 12th) or "invalid" according to its number.